# Admin Pages

The admin section is a separate sub-app under `/admin/*` with its own layout, color palette, and patterns.

## Access Control

- **Routing gate**: every admin route is wrapped in `<ProtectedRoute requiredAdmin />` inside `routes/AppRouter.jsx`. The gate redirects to `/login` if not signed in, and `/` if signed in without `is_admin`.
- **DB gate (RLS)**: every admin-only mutation must hit a table whose RLS policy allows `is_admin = true` on the requesting `auth.uid()`. The `profiles.is_admin` flag is the single switch.
- Promote a user via the Supabase SQL editor:
  ```sql
  update public.profiles set is_admin = true where email = '...';
  ```

## Layout (`components/layout/AdminLayout.jsx`)

- 240 px fixed sidebar with `Logo` (`color="gold"`), nav links, sign-out at the bottom.
- Top bar shows admin's name + email + initials avatar.
- Background: `bg-admin-bg` (`#0A0A0A`). Surfaces: `bg-admin-surface` (`#141414`). Borders: `border-gold/10`.
- Active nav item: `bg-gold/10 text-gold border-l-2 border-gold`.

When adding a new admin route:
1. Add the lazy import + `<Route>` to `AppRouter.jsx`.
2. Add an entry to the `links[]` array in `AdminLayout.jsx` with a `lucide-react` icon.

## Color Overrides

Admin only. Don't use these on the storefront:

| Token | Hex | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `bg-admin-bg` | `#0A0A0A` | page bg, sidebar |
| `bg-admin-surface` | `#141414` | cards, table cells, inputs |
| `border-gold/10` | gold @ 10% | section dividers |
| `border-gold/30` | gold @ 30% | active borders |

Charts (Recharts) palette: `['#C6A97A', '#B79BBF', '#A8A17A', '#E8C6C6', '#2D133A']`. Tooltip style: `{ background: '#141414', border: '1px solid #C6A97A40', color: '#F6F3EE' }`. Grid lines: `#C6A97A10`. Axes: `#F6F3EE60`.

## Page Header Pattern

Every admin page starts with:

```jsx
<div className="flex items-end justify-between mb-8">
  <div>
    <div className="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-gold mb-1">{Eyebrow}</div>
    <h1 className="font-display text-3xl uppercase tracking-[0.15em]">{Title}</h1>
  </div>
  {/* Right-side action(s): "+ New Product" button, filters, export CSV, etc. */}
</div>
```

## Charts (Recharts only)

`Recharts` is installed for admin charts. Don't use it on the storefront (would bloat public bundles). The `AdminDashboard` page is the reference for line, pie, and bar charts. Always wrap in `<ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={260}>`.

## CRUD Pattern

CRUD pages use:
- A **table** rendered from a `useAdminXxx()` hook.
- A **modal** (`<Modal />`) for create + edit (same form, `editing` state holds the row or empty template).
- A **second modal** for destructive actions (delete confirmation), `size="sm"`.
- After every mutation: `toast.success(...)` then `setEditing(null)` + the hook's `load()` refresh.

Reference: `AdminProducts.jsx` for product CRUD.

```jsx
const { products, saveProduct, deleteProduct, toggleActive } = useAdminProducts()
const [editing, setEditing] = useState(null)   // null | row | { ...empty }
const [deleting, setDeleting] = useState(null)

await saveProduct(payload)            // upsert (id present = update)
await deleteProduct(id)
await toggleActive(id, !active)
```

Form values:
- Always coerce numbers with `Number(form.x) || 0` when persisting (HTML inputs return strings).
- Slugs: `slug: form.slug || slugify(form.name)`.
- Tags / image URLs come from textareas — split + filter empty before saving.
- After insert/update, **call the hook's `load()`** (or rely on the hook to do it) so the table refreshes.

## CSV Export

Use `downloadCSV(rows, filename)` from `lib/utils.js`. Reference: `AdminOrders.jsx` and `AdminCustomers.jsx`. Build a flat `rows` array — nested objects render as `[object Object]`.

## Page Inventory

| Path | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/admin` | `AdminDashboard.jsx` | KPI cards (revenue, orders, products, customers) + revenue line chart + status pie + top-products bar + recent orders table |
| `/admin/orders` | `AdminOrders.jsx` | Table, status filter, detail modal (update status + tracking), CSV export |
| `/admin/products` | `AdminProducts.jsx` | List, create/edit modal, delete confirm, toggle active |
| `/admin/stock` | `AdminStock.jsx` | Inline editable stock cells, low-stock highlight (`< 5`) |
| `/admin/customers` | `AdminCustomers.jsx` | Search + CSV export |
| `/admin/marketing` | `AdminMarketing.jsx` | Tabs: subscribers / send campaign / email logs / promo codes CRUD |

## Don'ts

- ❌ Don't import storefront layout components (`Navbar`, `Footer`, `CartDrawer`) into admin pages.
- ❌ Don't reuse `MainLayout` for admin routes.
- ❌ Don't put admin queries in a public hook — keep them in `useAdmin.js`.
- ❌ Don't use `bg-black` / `bg-ivory` for admin surfaces — use the `admin-bg` / `admin-surface` tokens.
- ❌ Don't ship admin pages without `<ProtectedRoute requiredAdmin />` — RLS is the second line of defense, not the first.
- ❌ Don't add destructive actions without a confirmation modal.
